f=Cybersecurity/bastion/custom/infra-vuln-management/SKILL.md · in=disciplined management CVEs security vulnerabilities across OS, cloud infrastructure, in-house systems distinct application dependencies (which ops patches) code-level vulnerabilities (which aegis handles). skill covers scan cadence, severity classification, patch SLAs, exception process infra-level findings. · h2:Boundary (Critical)=**ops (Engineering)** patches **app dependencies** (npm/pip/maven packages, library CVEs shipped code)., **bastion patches infra/OS/cloud** (kernel, packages, cloud service configs, container base images)., **aegis (Engineering)** handles **code-level vulnerabilities** (SAST/DAST findings application code)., skill covers infra/OS only. finding crosses boundaries (e.g., vuln container running app code), coordinate ops/aegis don't assume ownership. · p=Unpatched infrastructure common initial access vector real breaches. structured vulnerability management program defined scan cadences, severity thresholds, patch SLAs, exception processes turns "we need patch" fire drill routine. · wu=new CVE published affecting infrastructure stack., Schedule-driven vulnerability scan., "Are vulnerable X," "what's our patch status," "CVE-202X-XXXX.", Patch compliance reporting. · st:/ Protocol=`SCAN (on cadence: OS packages, cloud infra services, container base images, network appliances) \· → IDENTIFY (CVE \· affected asset \· severity per CVSS or vendor) \· → CLASSIFY (critical/high/medium/low per CVSS + business context) \· → PRIORITIZE (severity × exploitability × asset criticality) \· → TREAT (patch → ops/operator / mitigate → compensating control / accept → warden exception)` · in=**Scan cadence.** packages weekly, cloud infra monthly, container base images build. Scans scheduled, ad-hoc. **Severity CVSS business context.** critical CVE internet-facing system emergency; CVE isolated internal system high. Never downgrade severity CVE without documenting business context. **Patch SLAs (configurable, operator-set):** · in=**Critical** patch within days (or isolate compensating control), **High** patch within days, **Medium** patch within days, **Low** patch next scheduled cycle · in=**Exceptions time-boxed.** patch can't applied within SLA gets exception through warden's security-exception-process compensating control, expiry, owned. **Coordinate ops.** joint infra+app vulns, ops leads patch, bastion tracks finding. Don't patch app deps yourself. **Track everything.** CVE finding until asset confirmed patched. Partial patching (asset still reachable old version) resolved. **Trend reporting.** Patch compliance mean-time-to-patch, overdue exceptions metrics surface warden operator cadence. · of=`## Vuln Scan: [scope] — [date] \· Tool: [scanner name] \· Assets scanned: [count] \· Findings: \· Critical: [count] — top CVE: [ID \· asset \· CVSS \· SLA due] \· High: [count] — top CVE: [ID \· asset \· CVSS \· SLA due]` · pr=**Scan cadence, fire.** Scheduled scanning prevents emergency patching., **CVSS business context** severity number., **Patch SLAs binding** critical days, silent slippage., **Exceptions through warden.** self-approved patch delays., **Track everything.** unpatched CVE without tracking entry invisible., **Boundary ops hard.** Infra app-dependency defined seam, judgment call. · f=vuln scanner deployed manual CVE tracking against asset inventory, labeled "manual scanner." Flag risk warden., Can't patch within SLA route warden's exception process immediately don't let SLA lapse silently., Scanner coverage gap (some assets scanned) flag finding; partial coverage known risk. · b:with Other Skills=**cloud-posture** (sibling): CSPM covers cloud misconfigs; skill covers infra CVEs. public bucket cloud-posture; critical CVE EC2 instance hosting app skill., **hardening-baselines** (sibling): baselines define secure config; vuln management tracks patch status against them., **network-security** (sibling): network segmentation contains blast radius unpatched systems., **warden**: overdue patches, expired exceptions, SLA breaches register risks., **ops (Engineering)**: joint infra+app findings coordinate here; ops patches app deps separately., **aegis (Engineering)**: app/code-level vulns aegis, here.